I made this recipe earlier this week with pears we had received as a gift. Although my finished product didn't look anything like the photo on the website, it was very, very tasty! I used whole wheat flour and raw sugar. Cut the sugar to 2 TB since the pears were so ripe. Still absolutely wonderful taste. So for a party tonight, I substituted the regular AP flour with gluten free flour due to diet restrictions of our friends. The pastry didn't perform as nicely as with regular AP flour or whole wheat flour. So I'll stick with standard flour when I make this again.

Rating: 4
I have made this croustade 3 times. Every time the dish comes out beautiful and tasty and I get rave reviews. Generally, I make it according to the recipe, however, I have made a few changes. First, I always add 1-2 TBS of pear brandy to the fruit mixture. Really compliments the fruit. When I made the dish for Thanksgiving, I used half pears and half cranberries. The cranberries were sauteed in 2 TBS of butter until shiny, then I added 6 TBS of maple syrup and 1 tsp cinnamon. I cooked them until most of the liquid was absorbed but they still held their shape. I added these to the freshly cut pears. Wow, beautiful and tasty! You can not go wrong with this dish!

