I'm still new to making pastry so I was a bit apprehensive about making this even though it sounded easy enough. I had a problem with my butter not being cold enough so when combined with the flour, it didn't really crumble. I could see pieces of butter when I rolled out my pastry. The pieces melted while in the oven and made a bit of a mess in the pan, but the croustade was not worse for the wear. I did have to add more cream to keep the pastry from being too crumbly. The taste was great and it looked nice and rustic. For some reason, my pears turned slightly brown after it came out of the oven even with the addition of the lemon juice, but it wasn't a big deal. Overall it was yummy and I'd make it again.

